HOW TO :	Create a new color variation of the model

- Open a preset fish through GIMP 


- Select zones of a similar colour with the "Select by color tool"
	If needed :	-adjust the threshold to select a bigger zone
			-use Ctrl to add unselected areas of similar colour
- In the menu, under Colors, use "Hue-Chroma" menu to adapt the color of the zones to your preference.

-Export the result as JPEG (Ctrl+Shift+E)

-Edit the .mtl files to refer to your .jpg file (or edit the name of your jpg file to match).

-Having the .obj, .mtl and .jpg in the same folder add the folder to Unity and drag the Folder to your assets.
